  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: `Geth/v1.4.5-stable/linux/go1.5.1`\nOS & Version: Linux Ubuntu 14.04\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nBased on [https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Connecting-to-the-network](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Connecting-to-the-network) I understand that a new node after connecting to a node with existing peers should  establish connection with these nodes over time.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nOnly force (provided in static.json or by addPeer() command connection are established)\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n- add new node (no peers)\n- add a peer with `admin.addPeer()`\n- wait\n",
